      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "The surface of the snowpack will cool hardly at all during the overcast night. Sunshine and high temperatures will give rise as the day progresses to increasing and thorough wetting of the snowpack. This applies in all aspects below approximately 2400 m, as well as on sunny slopes at elevated altitudes. <br/> <br/> Isolated avalanche prone weak layers exist in the top section of the old snowpack. Towards its base, the snowpack consists of faceted crystals. This applies in particular on west, north and east facing slopes at high altitude, as well as in all aspects in high Alpine regions."
      },
      "source": {
        "provider": {
          "name": "LWD K\u00e4rnten",
          "website": "https://lawinenwarndienst.ktn.gv.at/?lang=en"
        }
      },
